<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 13:26:44 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>一名 13 岁男孩在田野里发现了这枚铜币。结果是在柏林发现的第一件古希腊文物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-13-year-old-boy-found-this-bronze-coin-in-a-field-it-turned-out-to-be-the-first-ancient-greek-artifact-discovered-in-berlin-180988627/</link><description>该物品于公元前三世纪在特洛伊铸造，可能是作为送给死者的礼物而埋葬的。考古学家不知道它是如何最终出现在现代德国的</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-13-year-old-boy-found-this-bronze-coin-in-a-field-it-turned-out-to-be-the-first-ancient-greek-artifact-discovered-in-berlin-180988627/</guid></item><item><title>一个新的美洲原住民 DNA 大数据库动摇了科学家关于南美洲人类住区的理论</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-big-database-of-dna-from-indigenous-americans-shakes-up-scientific-theories-about-human-settlement-of-south-america-180988628/</link><description>基因组数据为之前未知的移民浪潮提供了证据，生活在墨西哥中部和南部的土著群体从大约 1,300 年前开始蔓延到南美洲和加勒比地区</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-big-database-of-dna-from-indigenous-americans-shakes-up-scientific-theories-about-human-settlement-of-south-america-180988628/</guid></item><item><title>第二次世界大战期间，柏林大火烧毁了数百幅绘画。现在，博物馆将在线发布丢失艺术品的照片档案</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fires-in-berlin-destroyed-hundreds-of-paintings-during-world-war-ii-now-a-museum-will-publish-photo-archives-of-the-lost-artworks-online-180988621/</link><description>随着鲁本斯和卡拉瓦乔遗失画作的底片被数字化并在线发布，记录 Gemäldegalerie 藏品的积极努力将在一个世纪后得到回报</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 20:25:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fires-in-berlin-destroyed-hundreds-of-paintings-during-world-war-ii-now-a-museum-will-publish-photo-archives-of-the-lost-artworks-online-180988621/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，星际彗星 3I/ATLAS 来自银河系极其寒冷、孤独的区域</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/interstellar-comet-3i-atlas-came-from-an-extremely-cold-lonely-region-of-the-milky-way-galaxy-new-research-suggests-180988625/</link><description>天文学家分析了彗星接近太阳时散发出的蒸气，发现它含有大量“重”水。这暗示它是在一个寒冷的行星系统中长大的，可能在它的母星形成之前</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 19:26:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/interstellar-comet-3i-atlas-came-from-an-extremely-cold-lonely-region-of-the-milky-way-galaxy-new-research-suggests-180988625/</guid></item><item><title>一名游客在试图摸索大理石雕像时损坏了佛罗伦萨的“海王星喷泉”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-tourist-damaged-florences-fountain-of-neptune-while-attempting-to-grope-its-marble-statue-on-a-dare-180988623/</link><description>修复喷泉的马雕塑和饰带将花费近 6,000 美元。被指控的罪犯是最新一位为了应对同侪压力或追求社交媒体影响力而损坏艺术品的游客</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 17:52:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-tourist-damaged-florences-fountain-of-neptune-while-attempting-to-grope-its-marble-statue-on-a-dare-180988623/</guid></item><item><title>这种骨头嘎吱作响的章鱼几乎有一辆半卡车那么大，一亿年前可能以巨型爬行动物为食</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-bone-crunching-octopus-was-nearly-the-size-of-a-semitruck-and-may-have-feasted-on-giant-reptiles-100-million-years-ago-180988616/</link><description>根据对下颌化石的分析，这种巨大的无脊椎动物可能是顶级掠食者。这项工作表明，古代海洋并不像之前认为的那样完全由长有脊柱的生物统治</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 16:04:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-bone-crunching-octopus-was-nearly-the-size-of-a-semitruck-and-may-have-feasted-on-giant-reptiles-100-million-years-ago-180988616/</guid></item><item><title>观赏在马萨诸塞州海岸捕获的五千万分之一的彩色龙虾。它携带两组遗传信息</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-1-in-50-million-split-color-lobster-caught-off-the-coast-of-massachusetts-its-carrying-two-sets-of-genetic-information-180988615/</link><description>这种看起来不寻常的甲壳类动物有两种色调，一条线将其身体分为橙色的一面和棕色的一面。当两个受精的、未产下的龙虾卵接触时就会发生这种情况，导致其中一个吸收另一个</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-1-in-50-million-split-color-lobster-caught-off-the-coast-of-massachusetts-its-carrying-two-sets-of-genetic-information-180988615/</guid></item><item><title>尼安德特人有语言吗？新研究表明他们拥有像人类一样的基因硬件</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-neanderthals-have-language-new-research-suggests-they-had-the-genetic-hardware-for-it-like-humans-180988620/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，在人类语言发展中发挥作用的特定基因组区域在数十万年前就已经进化，当时人类和尼安德特人从共同祖先中分化出来之前</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-neanderthals-have-language-new-research-suggests-they-had-the-genetic-hardware-for-it-like-humans-180988620/</guid></item><item><title>国家许可的医用大麻已被重新归类为危险性较低的药物。这就是这意味着什么</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/state-licensed-medical-marijuana-has-been-reclassified-as-a-less-dangerous-drug-heres-what-that-means-180988617/</link><description>此举将使研究人员更容易研究该物质，并为获得许可的医用大麻经销商提供税收减免</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 20:32:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/state-licensed-medical-marijuana-has-been-reclassified-as-a-less-dangerous-drug-heres-what-that-means-180988617/</guid></item><item><title>世界上第一家人工智能艺术博物馆将在洛杉矶开幕，艺术界正在思考道德和可持续发展问题</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-worlds-first-museum-of-ai-art-will-open-in-los-angeles-as-the-art-world-ponders-questions-of-ethics-and-sustainability-180988613/</link><description>Dataland 的沉浸式展览由人工智能生成，将于 6 月 20 日向公众首次亮相，首场展览以数百万张自然图像为基础，介绍雨林</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 20:28:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-worlds-first-museum-of-ai-art-will-open-in-los-angeles-as-the-art-world-ponders-questions-of-ethics-and-sustainability-180988613/</guid></item><item><title>为了让航海者一号航天器继续其星际之旅，美国宇航局关闭了其为数不多的剩余仪器之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/to-keep-the-voyager-1-spacecraft-on-its-interstellar-journey-nasa-turned-off-one-of-its-few-remaining-instruments-180988608/</link><description>该探测器于近 50 年前发射，是距离地球最远的人造物体。关闭其中一台科学设备将有助于其节省能源并继续向太阳系边缘行进</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 18:59:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/to-keep-the-voyager-1-spacecraft-on-its-interstellar-journey-nasa-turned-off-one-of-its-few-remaining-instruments-180988608/</guid></item><item><title>我们为什么喜欢电影？这家新的“智能”电影院可追踪观众的脑电波和心率以找出答案</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-new-smart-movie-theatre-is-tracking-audiences-brain-waves-and-heart-rates-to-create-more-engaging-films-180988614/</link><description>布里斯托大学的研究人员正在通过将一家剧院变成生物识别实验室来研究电影观看体验的吸引力</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 18:20:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-new-smart-movie-theatre-is-tracking-audiences-brain-waves-and-heart-rates-to-create-more-engaging-films-180988614/</guid></item><item><title>海狸是生态系统工程师，它们可能成为对抗人为气候变化的有用盟友</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/beavers-are-ecosystem-engineers-and-they-might-be-helpful-allies-in-the-fight-against-human-caused-climate-change-180988609/</link><description>新的研究表明，勤劳的啮齿动物创造的湿地是碳汇，这意味着它们储存了大量的吸热二氧化碳——人类产生的气体是当今全球变暖的主要原因</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 14:36:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/beavers-are-ecosystem-engineers-and-they-might-be-helpful-allies-in-the-fight-against-human-caused-climate-change-180988609/</guid></item><item><title>是什么杀死了尼安德特人？新研究表明缺乏遗传多样性可能是部分原因</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/what-killed-the-neanderthals-new-research-suggests-a-lack-of-genetic-diversity-may-be-partially-to-blame-180988612/</link><description>当气候变冷时，尼安德特人的人口减少了。大多数生活在 60,000 至 40,000 年前的生物都是同一血统的后裔，并且具有非常相似的 DNA</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 14:04:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/what-killed-the-neanderthals-new-research-suggests-a-lack-of-genetic-diversity-may-be-partially-to-blame-180988612/</guid></item><item><title>在欧洲和非洲之间的沉船墓地，考古学家发现了数千年来注定沉没的船只</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-graveyard-of-shipwrecks-between-europe-and-africa-archaeologists-discovered-vessels-doomed-over-thousands-of-years-180988605/</link><description>一项新的考古调查显示，直布罗陀海峡的“港口”是古罗马、中世纪和二战沉船的最后安息地</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-graveyard-of-shipwrecks-between-europe-and-africa-archaeologists-discovered-vessels-doomed-over-thousands-of-years-180988605/</guid></item><item><title>日本找到了 1200 年樱花数据的新管家，维持气候变化研究项目</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-japan-a-new-steward-for-1200-years-of-cherry-blossom-data-has-been-found-sustaining-a-climate-change-research-project-180988607/</link><description>去年夏天去世的气候科学家青野康幸学会了阅读古代日本文字，以汇编可追溯到公元九世纪的盛花期记录</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 20:56:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-japan-a-new-steward-for-1200-years-of-cherry-blossom-data-has-been-found-sustaining-a-climate-change-research-project-180988607/</guid></item><item><title>火星探测器发现了这颗红色星球上前所未见的生命基石，为古代宜居性提供了证据</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-mars-rover-found-building-blocks-of-life-never-seen-on-the-red-planet-before-boosting-the-case-for-ancient-habitability-180988610/</link><description>美国宇航局好奇号探测器发现的有机分子可能是由生命形成的，但它们也可能来自地质过程或陨石</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 20:10:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-mars-rover-found-building-blocks-of-life-never-seen-on-the-red-planet-before-boosting-the-case-for-ancient-habitability-180988610/</guid></item><item><title>直布罗陀著名的猴子正在吃泥土，可能会缓解因咀嚼游客垃圾食品而引起的胃痛</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gibraltars-famous-monkeys-are-eating-dirt-likely-to-alleviate-stomach-aches-from-munching-on-tourists-junk-food-180988606/</link><description>英国境内的巴巴里猕猴是欧洲唯一的野生猴子。但许多人正在食用热量、糖、盐和乳制品含量高、纤维含量低的人类零食</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 19:51:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gibraltars-famous-monkeys-are-eating-dirt-likely-to-alleviate-stomach-aches-from-munching-on-tourists-junk-food-180988606/</guid></item><item><title>十年来首次在洪都拉斯山脉发现罕见的“云美洲虎”，代表环保主义者的胜利</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-rare-cloud-jaguar-was-spotted-in-honduran-mountains-for-the-first-time-in-a-decade-representing-a-win-for-conservationists-180988595/</link><description>这种大型猫科动物很少出现在高海拔地区，因此这一目击事件表明保护该地区野生动物走廊的努力正在发挥作用</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 15:37:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-rare-cloud-jaguar-was-spotted-in-honduran-mountains-for-the-first-time-in-a-decade-representing-a-win-for-conservationists-180988595/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家在 1,600 年前的埃及木乃伊包裹物中挖掘出《伊利亚特》的纸莎草碎片</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-unearth-a-papyrus-fragment-from-the-iliad-tucked-inside-the-wrappings-of-a-1600-year-old-egyptian-mummy-180988603/</link><description>荷马史诗的摘录以他的船只目录为特色，这是一段著名的段落，列出了航行到特洛伊的希腊军队。这可能是在木乃伊化背景下发现的第一个希腊文学文本</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 15:07:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-unearth-a-papyrus-fragment-from-the-iliad-tucked-inside-the-wrappings-of-a-1600-year-old-egyptian-mummy-180988603/</guid></item></channel></rss>